article.headline: San Francisco 60, Sacramento State 47
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Alvin Broussard had 13 points and a career-high 20 rebounds in San Francisco's 60-47 victory over Sacramento State on Saturday night. James Bayless had 22 points and 10 rebounds for the Dons (10-6), who opened the second half with a 16-3 run despite playing without two starters in both teams' final non-conference game. Brandon Guyton had 10 points for the Hornets (6-7), but the rest of the starters went 2-for-14. Jameel Push added nine points and seven rebounds in a reserve role. The Dons' senior forwards controlled the paint in San Francisco's seventh win in nine games. Bayless scored 13 points in the second half, finishing one point shy of his career high, and Broussard had 10 rebounds in each half of the Dons' second-biggest win of the season. Jason Gaines and Michigan transfer Dommanic Ingerson scored seven points apiece for San Francisco. Sacramento State dropped to 1-6 on the road this season with 32 percent shooting and nine first-half turnovers. The Hornets still are off to their best start since the 1999-00 season. Sacramento State scored the last 11 points of the game for a respectable final score. The Dons played without starting forward Tyrone Riley, who went home to Los Angeles for a family funeral. Guard John Cox, an all-conference selection last season, still hasn't played after injuring his knee in the season opener.
